    {
      "id": "aLJB",
      "code_hash": "313511a98aef809aedc5aa732be3edb9",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"8-notes-limitations\">8 \u00b7 Notes &amp; Limitations</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>The simulation is <strong>deterministic</strong>. A stochastic variant (Beta-distributed\n   hold-success per minute, Monte Carlo over uncertain point values) would\n   produce distributional outputs rather than point estimates.</li>\n<li><strong>Only one chest at a time</strong> can be in transit from Winterfell per the game\n   rules.  The model enforces this.</li>\n<li>The model does <strong>not</strong> account for combat buffs from Hot Spring / Armory,\n   troop strength decay, or healing mechanics.</li>\n<li><strong>Temporal reallocation</strong> (shifting from buildings-heavy in Period 1 to\n   chests-heavy in Period 2) is not modelled; the current version uses a\n   static allocation for the full 60 minutes.</li>\n<li>Building point values are <strong>placeholders</strong>.  Update them from in-game\n   screenshots for calibrated recommendations.</li>\n</ol></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    }
  ]
